{
  "texts": [
    "While ToMe extends the context window to about 5K frames, TransV efficiently scales beyond 10K frames.",
    "Figure 6.6Figure 6.",
    "Comparison of prefilling time.",
    "TransV incurs no additional latency at low frame inputs (e.g., 64 frames) while significantly reducing prefilling time at high frame inputs.",
    "For instance, at 4,096 frames, TransV reduces prefilling time by 15.7% compared to the ToMe baseline."
